{"id":"679945ab-0eb5-4ebe-9170-6025ed02e32c","type":"main-list-block","metadata":{"filename":"1512-10-[679945ab].json","folder":"michelangelo-letters"},"blockProperties":[],"children":[{"id":"1ec7c9a1-56fc-4419-b5d6-0ddf1fc46e1f","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"From Rome, [October, 1512].\r","standoffProperties":[{"id":"402b6a0f-e327-4df9-8830-4f361ea9afce","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":5,"end":8,"value":"501a8a32-2c8a-4934-9060-8c7e36339f0f","text":"Rom","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false},{"id":"15bafc9d-15b3-4a5d-bccd-fa5c5c2d88c0","type":"codex/time-reference","start":12,"end":24,"value":"d9f5c783-bf5d-43b0-9065-9b6d7dd4cdae","text":"October, 151","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false}],"blockProperties":[{"id":"499a8512-f331-4631-a904-f16f976bf2d5","type":"block/alignment/right","metadata":{},"isDeleted":false}],"children":[],"metadata":{},"relation":{}},{"id":"c8eb608a-998b-4b16-b9f9-049f642127e2","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"To Lodovico di Buonarrota Simoni,\r","standoffProperties":[{"id":"40bf0bbf-dc4a-44fa-ac18-d3707f4dcd00","type":"style/italics","start":0,"end":31,"value":"","text":"To Lodovico di Buonarrota Simon","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false},{"id":"5f51c6ed-8720-47c8-941a-4927c90dd3d6","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":31,"value":"21671569-3eea-412b-85cc-08f659f58019","text":"Lodovico di Buonarrota Simon","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false}],"blockProperties":[{"id":"2fadc1b7-5e1c-476e-aa45-3d7c00a16de9","type":"block/alignment/right","metadata":{},"isDeleted":false}],"children":[],"metadata":{},"relation":{}},{"id":"171af834-a5e1-4464-9c3c-2a7b80deb5f9","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"in Florence.\r","standoffProperties":[{"id":"c37b2129-72fa-49f0-bf7b-f93473e9618b","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":10,"value":"671ee7e7-ae1b-4a5a-9591-b40203d5108f","text":"Florenc","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false}],"blockProperties":[{"id":"1f1c8380-2220-49bc-8f2c-f7233422e65f","type":"block/alignment/right","metadata":{},"isDeleted":false}],"children":[],"metadata":{},"relation":{}},{"id":"ec3484aa-e859-453a-952d-dcbbdad1fd96","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"","standoffProperties":[],"blockProperties":[],"children":[],"metadata":{},"relation":{}},{"id":"e7313388-38f7-4582-9116-12b8816d2470","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"Dearest Father, — Your last letter informs me of all that is happening in Florence, although I already knew something. We must be patient, commit ourselves to God, and repent of our sins; for these adversities do not proceed from any other cause, and are chiefly due to pride and ingratitude. I never had to do with a more ungrateful and arrogant people than the Florentines. If, therefore, a judgment fall on us, it is but reasonable. As for the sixty ducats you tell me you have to pay, I think it very unfair and I am exceedingly angry. However, we must have patience for as long as it please God to let us be plagued. I will write a few lines to Giuliano de' Medici and enclose them in this letter. Read them through, and if you think it well to take them to him, do so, and see if they are of any service. If they are unavailing, consider whether you could sell what we have and take up your abode elsewhere. If you should find that you have been more heavily dealt with than other folk, do all you can to avoid paying, and let them rather take everything you possess: let me know what happens. But if you find that others have received exactly the same treatment, be patient and trust in God. You say you have already put together thirty ducats: take another thirty from my money and send me what remains. Take it to Bonifazio Fazi, and he will instruct Giovanni Balducci to pay me here: get Bonifazio to give you a form of receipt for the said money and send it here to me enclosed in your next letter. Look to your life and health, and if you cannot share the honours of the land like other citizens, be content that you have bread to eat; and live well with Christ, and poorly, as I do here. I live in a miserable fashion, caring neither for life nor for honours — the world, that is — and I suffer excessive hardships, assailed by a thousand anxieties. It is now about fifteen years since I had an hour's repose, and all that I have ever done has been to help you: and you have never recognised this nor believed it. God pardon us all! I am ready to go on doing as I have done as long as I live, provided I am able.\r","standoffProperties":[{"id":"1aed090c-3334-4ac0-9f07-f459ca8c0325","type":"style/uppercase","start":0,"end":13,"value":"","text":"Dearest Fathe","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false},{"id":"b5ccb4cf-1d44-48bd-b0a0-337282087ff8","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":13,"value":"21671569-3eea-412b-85cc-08f659f58019","text":"Dearest Fathe","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false},{"id":"d003d78e-febe-45ac-92fb-14539704a058","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":18,"end":21,"value":"21671569-3eea-412b-85cc-08f659f58019","text":"You","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false},{"id":"b4cbaad7-f3c8-44e5-9228-aa42bc46971e","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":43,"end":44,"value":"add92e01-cefe-4f13-94dd-f00eb82155b0","text":"m","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false},{"id":"37a5ece4-8cb9-4cf3-a2da-baee2b1e2f75","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":71,"end":72,"value":"0c663cc2-dd9f-40ce-b17b-734e41b369ef","text":"i","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false},{"id":"579b8199-076e-4919-957a-79383db31785","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":74,"end":81,"value":"671ee7e7-ae1b-4a5a-9591-b40203d5108f","text":"Florenc","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false},{"id":"504a93bf-74d9-4d8f-b123-3c5f209d5fa1","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":93,"end":93,"value":"add92e01-cefe-4f13-94dd-f00eb82155b0","text":"","metadata":{},"plugin":null,"isDeleted":false},{"id":"e67c727f-5dfb-467e-b97e-0eb45a3074fc","type"